honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class MediaLabel_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.MediaLabel_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MediaLabel_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Media Label data from an KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    MTMedia Type
    MLMaximum Label Length
    CLContinuous Label Length
    STSensor Type
    POPaper Empty Distance
    LWLabel Width
    HCHead Cleaning Threshold
    RLRibbon Low Diameter
    RPRibbon Low Pause
    TPLabel Length Limit
    PBPresent Backup
    PDPresent Location/Distance
    KDBackup Location/Distance
    SLStop Location
    BABackup After Print
    GAGap Alternate Mode
    LBAuto Align
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        • Constructor Detail

          • MediaLabel_DPL

            public MediaLabel_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
            The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

            Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

            Parameters:
            conn - connection to printer
